  "prompt": "What is the best time to visit Kanniyakumari?",
  "response": "Kanniyakumari, located at the southernmost tip of India, is a popular tourist destination known for its scenic beauty and cultural significance. The best time to visit Kanniyakumari is during the winter months, from October to March, when the weather is pleasant and ideal for sightseeing and outdoor activities. During these months, the temperature ranges from 17\u00b0C to 32\u00b0C, making it comfortable for exploring the town and its attractions.\n\nThe monsoon season, from June to September, brings heavy rainfall, which might hinder travel plans and outdoor excursions. Although the landscape becomes lush and green, it may not be the best time for tourists who want to spend time outside.\n\nThe summer months, from April to May, can be quite hot and humid, with temperatures soaring up to 35\u00b0C or higher. This may not be ideal for tourists who prefer cooler weather.\n\nTo summarize, October to March is generally considered the best time to visit Kanniyakumari for a comfortable and enjoyable experience.",
